t","text":"Modeled Writing "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Write and read aloud short sentences about the different seasons."}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge-box","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_hed_support-challenge","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Support "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_numbers","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"1"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"What happens to trees in the fall? "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge-box","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_numbers","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"2"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"In the fall, the leaves change c"},{"type":"element","name":"fill-in-the-blank","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"___"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(color)"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge-box","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_numbers","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"3"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"In the fall, the leaves change color."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge-box","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_hed_support-challenge","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Challenge "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"What is one change that happens in the next season?"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"child-development-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_hed-green","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Child Development: Ordinal Terms "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_body","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Knowing ordinal terms ("},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_emphasis","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"first, second, third,"}]},{"type":"text","text":" etc.) allows children to understand and to communicate the orders or placements of people or things. The ordinals “first,” “second,” and “third” are different from the cardinal numbers “one,” “two,” and “three,” so children often need to learn and practice these terms separately."}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"day_2","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"week","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header_all-caps","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"OUR EARTH"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_header_separator","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"|"}]},{"type":"text","text":"  WEEK 2: Seasons"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"circle-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_2","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Share the Mind Builder: Use Imagination "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"When we use our imaginations, we make pictures in our minds. We can imagine things that are real, like what our house looks like, and we can imagine things that are not real, like a princess riding a dragon. That’s the great thing about using your imagination. You can picture anything you like! "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_2","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Focus on Vocabulary "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Introduce new vocabulary.  "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use 7.2.2 Vocabulary Card. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_vocab_words","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"imagine"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"story-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Connect to the Book "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Show the big book cover. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Today we will revisit some pages of "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The Things That I LOVE About TREES"}]},{"type":"text","text":" by Chris Butterworth and illustrated by Charlotte Voake. We will practice using our imaginations as we read. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the Clifford Puppet. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Clifford loves to use his imagination to picture what happens in books. "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Close-Read: Connect to the Mind Builder "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Focus on Counting: Review ordinal terms with children, and use them to describe seasons.  On this second read, include some of the information in the smaller text. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 8–9 "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"What season is shown first in this book? The blossoms on the tree are buzzing with bees. What do you imagine that sounds like? Can you imagine how the flowers smell? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_highlight_teacher_inst_Italic","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"imagine "}]},{"type":"text","text":"Vocabulary Card. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 14–15 "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The second season in the book is summer. The wind blows the trees. What do you imagine that looks and sounds like? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"What else happens in the summer?  "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 22–23 "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"What season is third in this book?  "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s imagine that the leaves are falling from the tree and we are trying to catch them. Here they come! "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 26–27 "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The fourth season is winter. During winter many trees lose their leaves. Imagine standing next to a giant tree on a snowy day. Let’s look up—can you see the sky through the trees? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"page 28 "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"There are so many things we can do with trees! Imagine you were going to play with a tree in spring. What would you play first? What would you play second? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Extended Play "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Divide children into four groups, one for each season. Encourage each group to use their imaginations to act out various activities you can do in the different seasons. Provide examples such as swimming and eating ice cream in the summer, raking up leaves in the fall, or planting a garden in the spring. Give groups time to decide what they will act out before they share.  "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Shared Writing "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Transcribe children’s speech as they talk about the different seasons."}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"child-development-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_hed-green","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Child Development: Use Imagination "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_body","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"When children use their imagination, they practice expressing themselves (both verbally and nonverbally), interacting, reacting, and trying out different roles. Using their imaginations and trying new ways of doing things helps children develop critical thinking skills and encourages creative problem-solving. (www.brighthorizons.com/family-resources)"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"day_3","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"week","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header_all-caps","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"our earth"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_header_separator","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"|"}]},{"type":"text","text":"  WEEK 2: Seasons"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"circle-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_3","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Share the Math Strategy  "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Practice location words by playing a game of "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_emphasis","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Simon Says"}]},{"type":"text","text":". For example, Simon says put your hands on top of your head. Put your hands over your eyes, and so on. "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_3","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Top and Bottom "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use blocks to teach "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_emphasis","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"top"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_emphasis","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"bottom"}]},{"type":"text","text":". Stack three to five blocks and ask children to point to the top and bottom blocks. Repeat, ordering the blocks differently each time. "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_3","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Focus on Vocabulary "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Introduce new words. "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use 7.2.3 Vocabulary Cards. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_vocab_words","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"top bottom"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"story-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit the Book  "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Show the big book cover. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Today we are going to reread "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The Things That I LOVE About TREES"}]},{"type":"text","text":" by Chris Butterworth and illustrated by Charlotte Voake. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the Lala Stick Puppet. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Lala wants to learn more about trees and the seasons! "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Ask the Guiding Question "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The leaves change throughout the year. As we read today, I want you to think about this guiding question: What is one way that leaves change in a season?  "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Read-Aloud: Focus on Spatial Sense "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"As you read, pause to ask about the positions of children and objects. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 10–11 "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The children are pointing at the top of the tree. What do the leaves in this picture look like? "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_highlight_teacher_inst_Italic","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"top "}]},{"type":"text","text":"Vocabulary Card. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"page 13 "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The children look tiny standing at the bottom of the tree. There are big roots underground, below the bottom of the tree."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_highlight_teacher_inst_Italic","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"bottom "}]},{"type":"text","text":"Vocabulary Card. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 14–15 "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"How do the leaves change in the summer?  "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"page 21 "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Look at the bird. Is it near the top or the bottom of the tree?  "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 22–23 "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"What happens to the leaves in fall? Are they still on the tree? Where do they go?  "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"page 24 "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"What happens to the leaves in winter? The girl is at the bottom of the tree looking up at the top. What does she see? How is it different from summer? "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Talk About It "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Did you think about the guiding question? What is one way that leaves change in a season? "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Have children "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Turn and Talk"}]},{"type":"text","text":". Then use Equity Sticks to select several children to share their responses with the class.  "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Possible responses: "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_bulleted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The leaves grow in spring. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_bulleted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The leaves are big in summer. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_bulleted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"There are no leaves in winter. "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Interactive Writing "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Share a pen with children as you draw and write together about the different seasons."}]}]}]},