ation is an important part of learning about the seasons, including outside exploration and discussion. While outside, children can make note of changes they see and then draw pictures of their observations in science journals."}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"day_5","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"week","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header_all-caps","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"our earth"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_header_separator","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"|"}]},{"type":"text","text":"  WEEK 2: Seasons"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"circle-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_5","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Connect to Science "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Ask children to talk about what they learned about the seasons. What did they already know about how trees change in the different seasons? "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_5","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Act It Out "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Invite children to act out an outdoor activity that can be done in each season. Have one child act out an activity and challenge the other children to guess what season it is. "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_5","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Focus on Vocabulary "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Introduce new words. "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":